I am going to make extreme examples.<br>
But it is to show young ppl how FG will go with reservation.<br>
Some stupid ppl just repeats&quot;Training spot...&quot;, &quot;40th ppl..&quot; etc etc<br>
never try to understand/imagine WHAT WILL HAPPEN ON THEM AFTER FEW MORE LEVELS.<br>
It's not personal rant, niether personal impatience.<br>
We had many troubles about FG, it means we can't make FG reservable anymore.<br>
World goes as it should go.<br>
Here are some ideas which is good to show ppl the future.<br>
<br>
Suggestion1:<br>
Let's start camping FG reservation board before Vote time limit comes.<br>
And let's show stupid ppl the VS nightmare.<br>
Since there is no replacement for cleric epic, and ppl are getting higher level,<br>
more and more ppl need to kill Ragefire.<br>
Now it's not too crowded, ppl can just do FG when it is not reserved.<br>
But it will be impossible when more and more clerics need Ragefire.<br>
Those clerics will be FORCED to reserve Fire giants(=Ragefire),<br>
if more clerics reserve FG another clerics are FORCED to reserve it also<br>
because they won't be able to get spot without Reservation.<br>
Reservation calls reservation, sooner or later board will be filled,<br>
it will be reserved 13 days 23 hours 59 min 59 sec before each raid like PoF/PoH.<br>
I think we need to show this to fools who can't understand this by discussion.<br>
Those ppl voting on YES think they can do FG if it is reservable.<br>
But they can't imagine that reservation crowd will makes it very hard to reserve itself.<br>
<br>
Suggestion2:<br>
Don't res those ppl voting on YES with your epic.<br>
And don't allow them to join any raid which would need res by the epic.<br>
Why?<br>
Simple reason.<br>
Voting on yes and asking res means...<br>
<br>
&quot;Go away high levels. I will block your Ragefire with FG reservation<br>
i don't care about you because i want FG to raise my skill!(and to get their lewts.*cough*)<br>
You will have huge trouble to get Ragefire and will be very frustrated.<br>
But chance is not 0 %. Just wait, be patient, try again and again to talk with them.<br>
Good luck on your epic.<br>
By the way, can i get res?&quot;<br>
<br>
Am i wrong?<br>
<br>
Suggestion3:<br>
Maybe it's too late, but i think we shouldn't allow indy ppl to vote on FG.<br>
Only ppl who shows their level/class/guild(&lt;-important) should vote.<br>
Raid is not 1 group hunt, raider needs any kind of organization and it is called guild.<br>
Indy person screams for reservation is nothing but ...<br>
Guildless_person_01 shouts&quot;I WANT NAGGY! IT'S MINE!&quot;<br>
Wipe out unknown ppl, list up known ppl in guild,<br>
and put those ppl on YES side for &quot;no res for you by epic&quot; list.<br>
Read suggestion2 for the reason.<br>
Another reason is there are too many unknown ppl on YES side as Lanos mentioned.<br>
As far as i can see, most of NO side ppl are high level and belong to any kind of guild.<br>
<br>
Please put any kind of reply or opinion.<br>
I can be wrong.<br>
But i don't need any unproductive reply like &quot;it is good for training&quot; anymore.<br>
What i am talking about is &quot;future vision&quot;.<br>
If it goes how, what will happen next,<br>
this is what i want to talk.<br>
If you are voting on YES, it's fine.<br>
Just explain how it will affect BOTH low and high level ppl.<br>
<br>
